er administers the portfolio through the [[Ministry of Education (Malaysia)|Ministry of Education ]].\n\nThe current Malaysian '''Minister of Higher Education''' is Dr. [[Noraini Ahmad]], since 10 March 2020. The minister is supported by Deputy Minister of Higher Education, whom is Dr. [[Mansor Othman]]. The minister administers the portfolio through the [[Ministry of Higher Education (Malaysia)|Ministry of Higher Education ]].\n\n==List of ministers of education==\nThe following individuals have been appointed as Minister of Education, or any of its precedent titles:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moe.gov.my/index.php/my/korporat/senarai-menteri-pendidikan|title=Former Minister of Education|date=|publisher=Ministry of Education, Malaysia|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''Political Party:'''\n{{legend2|{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}|[[Alliance Party (Malaysia)|Alliance]]/[[Barisan Nasional|BN]]|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}|[[Pakatan Harapan|PH]]|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|{{Malaysian United Indigenous Party/meta/color}}|[[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|PPBM]]|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=2|Portrait\n! Name<br /><small>(Birth\u2013Death)<br>Constituency</small>\n! Political Party\n! Title\n! Took Office\n! Left Office\n! [[Prime Minister of Malaysia|Prime Minister]]<br /><small>(Cabinet)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Alliance Party (Malaysia)/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| [[File:Tun Abdul Razak (MY 2nd PM).jpg|100px]]\n| [[Abdul Razak Hussein]]<br><small>(1922\u20131976)</small>\n| [[Alliance Party (Malaysia)|Alliance]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]])\n| rowspan=19|Minister of Education\n| 1952\n| 1957\n| ''Chief Minister of the<br/> Federation of Malaya''<br/>[[Tunku Abdul Rahman]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Alliance Party (Malaysia)/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| \n| [[Khir Johari]]<br><small>(1923\u20132006)<br>MP for