ce                = \n| seat                     = [[Putrajaya]]\n| nominator                = \n| appointer                = [[Yang di-Pertuan Agong]] on the recommendation of the [[Prime Minister of Malaysia]]\n| appointer_qualified      = \n| termlength               = \n| termlength_qualified     = \n| constituting_instrument  = \n| precursor                = \n| formation                = {{startdate|1955|df=y}}\n| first                    = [[Abdul Razak Hussein]]\n| last                     = \n| abolished                = \n| succession               = \n| abbreviation             = \n| unofficial_names         = \n| deputy                   = [[]]\n| salary                   = \n| website                  = {{URL|http://www.moe.gov.my/}}\n}}\nThe current Malaysian '''Minister of Education''' is Dr. [[Mohd Radzi Md Jidin]], since 10 March 2020. The minister is supported by Deputy Minister of Education, whom are Senator '''Dato' Dr. Mah Hang Soon''' and '''Muslimin Yahaya'''. The minister administers the portfolio through the [[Ministry of Education (Malaysia)|Ministry of Education ]].\n\nThe current Malaysian '''Minister of Higher Education''' is Dr. [[Noraini Ahmad]], since 10 March 2020. The minister is supported by Deputy Minister of Higher Education, whom is Dr. [[Mansor Othman]]. The minister administers the portfolio through the [[Ministry of Higher Education (Malaysia)|Ministry of Higher Education ]].\n\n==List of ministers of education==\nThe following individuals have been appointed as Minister of Education, or any of its precedent titles:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moe.gov.my/index.php/my/korporat/senarai-menteri-pendidikan|title=Former Minister of Education|date=|publisher=Ministry of Education, Malaysia|accessdate=14 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''Political Party:'''\n{{legend2|{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}|[[Alliance Party (Malaysia)|Alliance]]/[[Barisan Nasional|BN]]|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}|[[Pakatan 