und:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| [[File:Najib Razak 2008-08-21.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Najib Razak]]<br><small>(b. 1953)<br>MP for [[Pekan (federal constituency)|Pekan]]</small>\n| [[Barisan Nasional|BN]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]])\n| 1995\n| 1999\n| [[Mahathir Mohamad]]<br><small>(V)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| \n| [[Musa Mohamad]]<br><small>(b. unknown)<br>Senator</small>\n| [[Barisan Nasional|BN]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]])\n| 1999\n| 2004\n| [[Mahathir Mohamad]]<br><small>(VI)</small><br>[[Abdullah Ahmad Badawi]]<br><small>(I)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| [[File:Hishamuddin2014.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Hishammuddin Hussein]]<br><small>(b. 1961)<br>MP for [[Sembrong (federal constituency)|Sembrong]]</small>\n| [[Barisan Nasional|BN]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]])\n| 2004\n| 2009\n| [[Abdullah Ahmad Badawi]]<br><small>(II \u2022 III)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| [[File:MuhyiddinUS.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]<br><small>(b. 1947)<br>MP for [[Pagoh (federal constituency)|Pagoh]]</small>\n| [[Barisan Nasional|BN]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]])\n| 2009\n| 2015\n| [[Najib Razak]]<br><small>(I \u2022 II)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| [[File:Idris bin Jusoh.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Idris Jusoh]]<br><small>(b. 1955)<br>MP for [[Besut (federal constituency)|Besut]]</small>\n| [[Barisan Nasional|BN]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]])\n| Second Minister of Education\n| 2013\n| 2015\n| [[Najib Razak]]<br><small>(II)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| \n| [[Mahdzir Khalid]]<br><small>(b. 1960)<br>MP for [[Padang Terap (federal constituency)|Padang Terap]]</small>\n| [[Barisan Nasional|BN]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]])\n| rowspan=4|Minister of Education\n| 29 July 2015\n| 12 May 2018\n| [[Najib Razak]]<br><small>(II)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}; color:red\"| \n| [[File:Maszlee Malik (cropped).jpg|100px]]\n| [[Maszlee Malik]]<br><small>(b. 1974)<br>MP for [[Simpang Renggam (federal constituency)|Simpang Renggam]]</small>\n| [[Pakatan Harapan|PH]] ([[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|PPBM]])\n| 21 May 2018\n| 3 January 2020\n| [[Mahathir Mohamad]]<br><small>(VII)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}; color:red\"| \n| [[File:Mahathir 2019 (cropped).jpg|100px]]\n| [[Mahathir Mohamad]]<br><small>(b.1925)<br>MP for [[Langkawi (federal constituency)|Langkawi]]</small><br>''Acting''\n| [[Pakatan Harapan|PH]] ([[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|PPBM]])\n| 8 January 2020\n| 24 February 2020\n| [[Mahathir Mohamad]]<br><small>(VII)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Malaysian United Indigenous Party/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n|\n| Dr. [[Mohd Radzi Md Jidin]]<br><small>\n| [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|PPBM]]\n| 10 March 2020\n| ''Incumbent''\n| [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]<br><small>(I)</small>\n|}\n\n==List of ministers of higher education==\nThe following individuals have been appointed as Minister of Higher Education, or any of its precedent titles:\n\n'''Political Party:'''\n{{legend2|{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}|[[Alliance Party (Malaysia)|Alliance]]/[[Barisan Nasional|BN]]|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=2|Portrait\n! Name<br /><small>(Birth\u2013Death)<br>Constituency</small>\n! Political Party\n! Title\n! Took Office\n! Left Office\n! [[Prime Minister of Malaysia|Prime Minister]]<br /><small>(Cabinet)</small>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white\"| \n| [[File:Shafie Salleh.jpg|50px]]\n| [[Shafie Salleh]]<br><small>(b. 1946)<br>MP for [[Kuala Langat (federal constituency)|Kuala Langat]]</small>\n|